    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-01-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="13"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <head>13. Telegram From the Special Representative in Vietnam (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CGJL1" type="from">Collins</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                        >Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d13fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 751G.5/1–955. Top Secret; <gloss target="#t_niact1">Niact</gloss>.
                        Repeated to Paris. There is no time of transmission on the source
                        text.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1955</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2660. Reference <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 2766, Paris telegram
                    2870, repeated Saigon 443, <gloss target="#t_Embtels1">Embtel</gloss> 2554.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d13fn2">
                        <ref target="#d11">Documents 11</ref>, <ref target="#d10">10</ref>, and <ref
                            target="#d3">3</ref>, respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Greatly disturbed, as I indicated yesterday to <persName
                            corresp="#p_EGPHR1">Ely</persName>, that French are clearly stalling on
                        approval <persName corresp="#p_EGPHR1">Ely</persName>–<persName
                            corresp="#p_CGJL1">Collins</persName> minute of understanding. Proposal
                        contained in Paris telegram 2870 tantamount to complete rewrite our minute.
                        Should be particularly noted that no reference is made to granting autonomy
                        to Vietnamese forces. Furthermore, it includes <pb facs="0062" n="30"
                            xml:id="pg_30"/> circumscribing details which I refused to accept from
                            <persName corresp="#p_EGPHR1">Ely</persName> and which would tend to
                        hamstring implementation our training program. I am sure <persName
                            corresp="#p_EGPHR1">Ely</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_OD1"
                            >O’Daniel</persName> and I can develop common sense procedures on ground
                        here covering all points raised in French proposal. I urge flat refusal by
                        Department of French proposal. I will certainly not agree to it unless
                        specifically instructed by higher authority.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>As indicated in separate message to follow,<note n="3" xml:id="d13fn3"
                            >Telegram 2663, <hi rend="italic">
                                <ref target="#d13">infra</ref>
                            </hi>.</note>
                        <persName corresp="#p_EGPHR1">Ely</persName> stated categorically yesterday
                        that French Government had approved our minute of understanding. He also
                        reaffirmed agreement my proposal to negotiate directly with Vietnamese
                        Government as outlined my telegram 2554.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="strong">[</hi>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_CGJL1">Collins</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                    <hi rend="strong">]</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
